<span id="freeTextContainer472707637559295091">[4+] <i>The Quiet American</i> could be called &quot;The Ignorant American&quot; or &quot;The Arrogant American&quot; but the wry title sets the tone of the novel. Written in 1955, the novel is a searing look at the beginning of U.S. involvement in Vietnam through the eyes of a war-weary English journalist. If only we had heeded Greene&apos;s cautionary message! I&apos;m glad my book club is going to discuss this novel because there is so much going on under the surface to talk about.</span>
  <span id="freeText472707637559295091" style="display:none">[4+] <i>The Quiet American</i> could be called "The Ignorant American" or "The Arrogant American" but the wry title sets the tone of the novel. Written in 1955, the novel is a searing look at the beginning of U.S. involvement in Vietnam through the eyes of a war-weary English journalist. If only we had heeded Greene's cautionary message! I'm glad my book club is going to discuss this novel because there is so much going on under the surface to talk about.</span>
